Factors that drive price¶

'enginesize','curbweight','horsepower','highwaympg', 'carlength','carwidth','citympg','price'

engine size -- It is directly proportional to the price. As we increase the size, the price will increase. curb weight -- this is also highly correlate with price, with the value of 0.84. hourse power --It is directly proportional to the price. As we increase the size, the price will increase. highway mpg -- this is inversly proportional to the price, and the correlation value is -0.7. car length / car width -- that is also a important factor because if we increase the lenght and the width the cost will increase. city mpg -- this is negatively correlated with the price.
